1
00:00:06,172 --> 00:00:08,675
THIS STORY IS BASED ON TRUE EVENTS

2
00:00:08,758 --> 00:00:13,013
AND IS A WORK OF FICTION

3
00:00:57,766 --> 00:01:01,811
OVER 30,000 SUICIDES
SEVEN YEARS IN A ROW

4
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:38,681
Good morning, ma'am.

5
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:39,682
Good morning.

6
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:42,268
Good news. Last night's show was a hit.

7
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:44,062
It scored a 25.3 rating.

8
00:01:44,145 --> 00:01:46,648
- That's up two points from last week.
- Very good.

9
00:01:46,731 --> 00:01:49,192
I mean, you were absolutely
on fire last night.

10
00:01:49,275 --> 00:01:50,944
The ratings just skyrocketed throughout…

11
00:01:51,027 --> 00:01:52,487
<i>Kazuko Hosoki.</i>

12
00:01:53,029 --> 00:01:55,615
<i>The most famous fortune teller in Japan.</i>

13
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:59,953
<i>The lineup of people</i>
<i>who want her to read their fortunes</i>

14
00:02:00,036 --> 00:02:01,621
<i>has become endless.</i>

15
00:02:03,498 --> 00:02:07,710
<i>Her book on Six-Star Astrology</i>
<i>that she published in 1982</i>

16
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:10,421
<i>has sold over 50,000,000 copies.</i>

17
00:02:10,922 --> 00:02:13,091
<i>It's been recognized</i>
<i>by Guinness World Records</i>

18
00:02:13,174 --> 00:02:15,760
<i>as the best-selling fortune-telling book</i>
<i>on the globe.</i>

19
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:22,267
TOP RATINGS FOR SIX YEARS

20
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:24,561
<i>Once she started appearing</i>
<i>on variety shows,</i>

21
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:28,314
<i>her blunt and honest assessments</i>
<i>made her an immediate smash hit.</i>

22
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:31,151
<i>Now she reigns supreme</i>
<i>in the entertainment industry</i>

23
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:32,986
<i>as the queen of television ratings,</i>

24
00:02:33,069 --> 00:02:36,406
<i>having gained more wealth and fame</i>
<i>than most could ever dream of.</i>

25
00:02:38,491 --> 00:02:41,661
<i>Yet her arrogance,</i>
<i>a product of her success,</i>

26
00:02:41,744 --> 00:02:43,329
<i>has earned her many critics.</i>

27
00:02:44,414 --> 00:02:46,583
<i>Accusations of staged readings</i>
<i>and dumb-luck-guesswork</i>

28
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:49,586
<i>have grown from mere whispers</i>
<i>to major news articles,</i>

29
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:52,088
<i>as some accuse her of being a total fraud.</i>

30
00:02:53,631 --> 00:02:57,010
<i>So who is Kazuko Hosoki, really?</i>

31
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:03,558
<i>It's my job to write the complete story</i>

32
00:03:03,641 --> 00:03:05,393
<i>of this woman's life.</i>

33
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:10,440
Ms. Hosoki, good to see you.

34
00:03:10,523 --> 00:03:12,317
Good morning, Kawatani.

35
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,068
Yazawa, this young man is the editor

36
00:03:14,152 --> 00:03:16,863
who wants to publish the biography
I told you about.

37
00:03:16,946 --> 00:03:20,283
Oh. I'm looking forward to it.
It's good to meet you. I'm Yazawa.

38
00:03:20,366 --> 00:03:22,410
Yes, the chief director.
I'm Kawatani, sir.

39
00:03:22,493 --> 00:03:24,037
I heard you're here to observe the show.

40
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,663
- Please enjoy.
- Thank you very much.

41
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:28,708
Oh. By the way,
I'd like you to meet Uozumi.

42
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:29,751
She's the writer.

43
00:03:29,834 --> 00:03:32,795
Calling a novelist a "writer"
is a little offensive.

44
00:03:33,296 --> 00:03:34,589
Oh. I'm sorry.

45
00:03:35,089 --> 00:03:37,342
Uh, it's a pleasure to meet you, ma'am.
Here's my card--

46
00:03:37,425 --> 00:03:38,760
I don't need that.

47
00:03:39,260 --> 00:03:41,721
A novelist's business card is their work.

48
00:03:41,804 --> 00:03:43,806
And I've already read your book, Minori.

49
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:50,313
Brilliant work.
Good for you. I'm counting on you.

50
00:03:51,856 --> 00:03:53,650
Uh, thank you very much.

51
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,109
Nice to meet you, ma'am.

52
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,574
So people like yourself,

53
00:04:02,575 --> 00:04:06,287
who are born under the Saturn Plus sign,
are entering the Great Calamity Period,

54
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:08,915
which will last for the next three years.

55
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:14,504
So if you choose to marry now,
it'll kill you.

56
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:20,009
But I really wanna get married to someone
while I'm still in my twenties.

57
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:22,470
Well, you should've gotten married
last year, then.

58
00:04:22,553 --> 00:04:23,721
You almost did, didn't you?

59
00:04:23,805 --> 00:04:25,682
Wait, how'd you know about that?

60
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:28,184
Who do you think
you're talking to, sweetheart?

61
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:30,603
Of course she knows she's talking
to the great Kazuko Hosoki!

62
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:32,981
- Everyone in Japan knows who you are!
- Is that so?

63
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:36,693
So you did have someone.

64
00:04:37,193 --> 00:04:40,613
A man you almost married last year,
isn't that so?

65
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:44,742
Yeah, but he cheated. So I ended it.

66
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:46,077
You broke it off?

67
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,161
Yeah.

68
00:04:47,745 --> 00:04:51,666
And now, as if you've learned nothing,
you wanna go marry a new man?

69
00:04:52,166 --> 00:04:53,209
Why's that?

70
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:54,544
Hmm.

71
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:58,381
Well, as we all know, a woman hits 30
and her market value drops quickly.

72
00:04:58,464 --> 00:04:59,424
So, um, yeah.

73
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:02,927
My God, you're dumb.

74
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:04,846
You're just a big idiot.

75
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:08,641
Uh, ma'am, I think you should remember
we're on live TV, so maybe--

76
00:05:08,725 --> 00:05:10,935
What's wrong with calling an idiot
"an idiot" these days?

77
00:05:12,854 --> 00:05:14,480
Tell me.

78
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:18,693
Why do you wanna be married anyway?

79
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:21,988
Well, to be happy, of course.

80
00:05:22,071 --> 00:05:23,781
That's not the truth.

81
00:05:24,365 --> 00:05:28,244
You just look at marriage as something
to fill the void of insecurity inside you.

82
00:05:29,704 --> 00:05:31,164
You call yourself a comedian,

83
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:33,624
but you've got no real talent,
charm, or presence.

84
00:05:33,708 --> 00:05:36,044
No real appeal as a woman either.

85
00:05:36,127 --> 00:05:39,964
So you're clinging to the one quality
you still do possess, which is your youth.

86
00:05:41,424 --> 00:05:43,176
But here's the thing.

87
00:05:44,052 --> 00:05:47,847
Do you really wanna live your whole life
depending on men?

88
00:05:49,349 --> 00:05:52,894
A woman like yourself,
who makes no effort to better herself,

89
00:05:52,977 --> 00:05:55,730
is perfect fodder for some loser to use

90
00:05:55,813 --> 00:05:58,941
and then throw away
like an old pair of shoes.

91
00:06:00,234 --> 00:06:02,904
How dare you say something like that.
What the hell is wrong with you?

92
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:07,283
I say it because I'm the one
who can see your future clear as day.

93
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:12,538
If you don't change your ways immediately,

94
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:14,332
you'll kill yourself.

95
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,876
No matter what, I would never do that.

96
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:17,877
Yes, you will.

97
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:19,545
- I would not!
- You will!

98
00:06:27,553 --> 00:06:29,222
I don't need this.

99
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:36,729
If you don't wanna believe me,
that's fine.

100
00:06:38,648 --> 00:06:39,690
But…

101
00:06:45,696 --> 00:06:49,283
…you should know
that you're going straight to hell.

102
00:06:51,702 --> 00:06:54,163
Wow! You could
cut the tension in there with a knife,

103
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:55,123
it was so intense.

104
00:06:55,206 --> 00:06:57,917
Oh! I'm still buzzing from it. Right?

105
00:06:58,418 --> 00:07:00,545
That's what gets the crowd hooked.

106
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:03,381
- Truth is, the whole world's gone soft.
- Ah.

107
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:07,301
They're all petrified
to even tell off an entitled little girl.

108
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:10,847
That's why they love women like me
who aren't afraid to be blunt and honest.

109
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:12,181
Ah. Yes.

110
00:07:12,807 --> 00:07:16,602
Um, do you by any chance do check-ins
to make sure that woman's okay?

111
00:07:16,686 --> 00:07:18,312
Well, some of it was for show.

112
00:07:18,396 --> 00:07:19,897
But not all of it though.

113
00:07:20,398 --> 00:07:21,858
Of course not.

114
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:23,443
Oh.

115
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:25,403
Mm.

116
00:07:28,489 --> 00:07:30,366
You're awfully quiet over there.

117
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:34,745
If you've got questions, ask them now.
Before we get to the restaurant.

118
00:07:36,581 --> 00:07:38,749
Don't mind her. She's a little nervous.

119
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:40,501
- Right?
- Mm-hmm.

120
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:42,879
Tiara.

121
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:45,381
Down you go, dear.

122
00:07:56,684 --> 00:07:57,518
Sensei.

123
00:07:58,603 --> 00:07:59,854
I'm on my way now.

124
00:08:02,607 --> 00:08:04,525
Oh no. Is that so?

125
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:08,029
You're gonna make it up to me later,
though, am I right?

126
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:11,616
All right. Yeah, you better.

127
00:08:11,699 --> 00:08:12,992
Talk later. Bye.

128
00:08:13,784 --> 00:08:15,578
Was that the deputy prime minister?

129
00:08:15,661 --> 00:08:16,579
Mm-hmm.

130
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:21,876
Canceled. Said it was urgent
and that he's very sorry.

131
00:08:21,959 --> 00:08:25,129
You two wanna join instead?
We can get a head start on your book.

132
00:08:25,213 --> 00:08:28,591
I'm guessing you have a lot of questions.

133
00:08:29,425 --> 00:08:31,719
Wow. Thank you.
We'd love to take you up on that.

134
00:08:31,802 --> 00:08:32,970
- Um…
- Thank you.

135
00:08:33,804 --> 00:08:36,599
What would you say is the origin
of who you are at your core?

136
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:40,436
Oh, it's just you told me earlier to ask.

137
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:43,397
Sorry. I didn't mean
to dive in so suddenly.

138
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:45,483
You're amazing, ya know?

139
00:08:45,566 --> 00:08:48,194
I like how you just go for it.
It's very writer-like.

140
00:08:51,948 --> 00:08:53,616
The origin, huh?

141
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,082
You could say hunger.

142
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:03,084
Hunger?

143
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:07,255
Not knowing when you'll get your next meal
and the fear that goes along with that.

144
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:10,258
You two have no idea what that's like.

145
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:12,468
How terrifying it truly is.

146
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:30,152
Can you believe this whole damn place

147
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:35,199
was nothing more than burnt ruin
60 years ago?

148
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:58,723
Get outta here, you brats!
This is my business!

149
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:01,392
You can't stand around here!
Get lost! Shoo!

150
00:10:05,896 --> 00:10:07,189
Move, move, move!

151
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:08,858
- Out of the way, now!
- Get off!

152
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:11,569
Hey! It's mine! I said it's mine! Get off!

153
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:22,455
Let us through, please!

154
00:10:22,538 --> 00:10:25,082
- Excuse us.
- Sorry! Excuse us.

155
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:28,294
Coming through.
Please, sorry! Coming through.

156
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:30,504
Sorry!

157
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:31,881
Sorry, sorry!

158
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:34,759
Oh, sorry. Coming through. Excuse us.

159
00:10:34,842 --> 00:10:36,052
Sorry.

160
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:37,094
Excuse us.

161
00:10:41,599 --> 00:10:43,434
Akiko! Push! Come on!

162
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:47,938
Kazuko!

163
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:50,983
Hisao! Sachiko! Push harder! Come on!

164
00:11:10,419 --> 00:11:12,088
Hey, Kazuko.

165
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:14,507
I want food.

166
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:16,759
You've got to be patient like Sachiko.

167
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:19,762
You're a boy.
You're supposed to be strong, Hisao.

168
00:11:39,281 --> 00:11:40,991
- Excuse us.
- Excuse us.

169
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:43,619
- Sorry. Thank you.
- Sorry. Coming through. Thank you.

170
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:45,371
- Excuse us.
- Sorry.

171
00:11:45,454 --> 00:11:50,126
- Sorry. Coming through.
- Passing through. Excuse us.

172
00:12:08,477 --> 00:12:10,688
- Hey, Maiko!
- Oh! Hi, George!

173
00:12:10,771 --> 00:12:13,065
- It's been a while, huh?
- I missed you.

174
00:12:13,149 --> 00:12:15,651
Hey! I missed you too.
Come on, I'll give you a ride.

175
00:12:15,735 --> 00:12:17,486
- Oh really?
- Yeah, come on.

176
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:18,696
Please?

177
00:12:18,779 --> 00:12:21,949
<i>This country was destroyed.</i>
<i>Completely ruined.</i>

178
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:26,454
<i>All because of the men</i>
<i>who started a war they could never win.</i>

179
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:30,750
<i>And, of course,</i>
<i>we all know who ended up paying the price.</i>

180
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:32,918
<i>The women?</i>

181
00:12:33,627 --> 00:12:35,212
<i>Exactly.</i>

182
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:40,634
<i>Somehow, someway, it's always the women</i>
<i>who draw the short straw.</i>

183
00:12:59,528 --> 00:13:02,114
Kazuko! What are you doing
just standing there?

184
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:03,491
Come give me a hand!

185
00:13:07,661 --> 00:13:09,497
You're opening a bar here?

186
00:13:10,331 --> 00:13:12,625
Yes, and we're gonna build it ourselves.

187
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:13,793
Me too?

188
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:16,837
Yes, all of us. Now, come on. Get to work.

189
00:13:16,921 --> 00:13:18,005
Come here.

190
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:23,803
<i>We didn't care what anyone else thought.</i>

191
00:13:25,387 --> 00:13:27,681
<i>We took things one day at a time.</i>

192
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:30,643
<i>The only thing</i>
<i>we cared about was survival.</i>

193
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:09,473
Please! I'm very sorry! I'm sorry!

194
00:14:15,354 --> 00:14:16,689
You have my word.

195
00:14:16,772 --> 00:14:19,066
I'll pay you back in full next week.

196
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:22,278
You got anything you can sell now?

197
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,697
Scrape together a little cash?

198
00:14:26,907 --> 00:14:30,995
I already sold my last kimono
and bought these.

199
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:35,499
So you blew your last bit of money
on these, did ya?

200
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:39,962
And this imported beer
turned out to be barley tea, huh?

201
00:14:44,008 --> 00:14:45,384
You're an idiot.

202
00:14:48,178 --> 00:14:50,222
I'd say go whore yourself out.

203
00:14:53,058 --> 00:14:55,811
But I know no one
would waste their money on you.

204
00:14:58,606 --> 00:15:00,858
In this life,
the weak, like you, get preyed on.

205
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:04,278
These days,
the people that get themselves conned

206
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:07,156
are more at fault
than the ones who do the conning.

207
00:15:28,135 --> 00:15:29,178
Good to go?

208
00:16:18,852 --> 00:16:20,562
Hisao. Come on.

209
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:21,605
Huh?

210
00:16:32,032 --> 00:16:35,786
Our father told us
that he got those from GHQ.

211
00:16:36,537 --> 00:16:38,455
He told us not to come back

212
00:16:38,956 --> 00:16:41,125
until we sold every single bottle.

213
00:16:51,135 --> 00:16:53,053
Ah, sure. Why not?

214
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:58,017
Twenty yen each.

215
00:16:59,643 --> 00:17:01,020
Four hundred total.

216
00:17:05,482 --> 00:17:06,525
50 yen.

217
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:08,986
Per bottle. 1,000 total.

218
00:17:09,486 --> 00:17:11,030
It's American beer, ya know.

219
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:20,122
Okay, then.

220
00:17:32,509 --> 00:17:34,470
- Thank you! Have a nice day!
- Thank you, sir. Ow!

221
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:48,984
That's barley tea!

222
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:51,653
Stupid brats tried to trick me!

223
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:53,072
Hold it!

224
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:54,782
Get back here, you little…

225
00:17:54,865 --> 00:17:56,825
Hey! Stop right there!

226
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:58,577
Get back here, you stupid kids!

227
00:17:58,660 --> 00:18:00,037
Outta my way! Move!

228
00:18:00,537 --> 00:18:02,206
- Get outta the way!
- Hurry!

229
00:18:02,289 --> 00:18:04,875
Stop! Give me my money, you little shits!

230
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:06,168
Stop running!

231
00:18:06,835 --> 00:18:08,087
Come back!

232
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:09,797
- Hey!
- It hurts!

233
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,632
Hisao! You okay?

234
00:18:12,257 --> 00:18:13,550
You little thieves!

235
00:18:13,634 --> 00:18:16,220
Give me my money,
or I'll turn you over to the police!

236
00:18:16,303 --> 00:18:18,514
- Give it! Give it back now!
- Stop!

237
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:20,265
Give me my money! Let go of it!

238
00:18:20,349 --> 00:18:23,060
Hey, give that back! That's my money!

239
00:18:23,977 --> 00:18:25,145
Give it back!

240
00:18:27,856 --> 00:18:29,608
Get off of me!

241
00:18:41,537 --> 00:18:42,371
Crazy girl.

242
00:18:43,413 --> 00:18:44,748
What's wrong with you?

243
00:19:12,901 --> 00:19:16,572
Why were you being so stupid?
Going off on your own like that?

244
00:19:17,072 --> 00:19:20,075
Your brother and you are too young
to be trying to sell fake stuff.

245
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:22,161
Akiko, Kazuko was just trying to help.

246
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:25,664
She could've gotten herself
and Hisao arrested. Perhaps much worse.

247
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:28,500
It's my fault. I'm sorry, sweetheart.

248
00:19:28,584 --> 00:19:29,710
Forgive me.

249
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:34,047
Mom.

250
00:19:34,631 --> 00:19:35,465
Yes?

251
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:39,428
In this life,
the weak get preyed on, right?

252
00:19:40,304 --> 00:19:42,472
People that get conned are more at fault.

253
00:19:43,056 --> 00:19:45,184
Listen. It's never right to con people.

254
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:47,811
Remember, God is always watching us
from above.

255
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:52,482
Kazuko.

256
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:56,486
People who choose to do bad things
go straight to hell.

257
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:25,933
Are you awake?

258
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:29,019
Sh! Go to sleep.

259
00:20:30,354 --> 00:20:32,481
I can't. I need food.

260
00:20:33,565 --> 00:20:34,983
Me too.

261
00:20:35,859 --> 00:20:37,653
I'm so hungry.

262
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:48,974
Here.

263
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:53,020
What about you?

264
00:21:53,645 --> 00:21:55,272
Oh, don't worry about me.

265
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:06,366
I'm fine.

266
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:08,660
Go on. It's okay.

267
00:22:31,808 --> 00:22:33,018
Forgive me.

268
00:23:40,210 --> 00:23:42,087
<i>For the rest of my life,</i>

269
00:23:43,505 --> 00:23:46,007
<i>I'll never forget</i>
<i>the taste of that earthworm.</i>

270
00:23:46,591 --> 00:23:48,552
<i>It was the taste of survival.</i>

271
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:06,319
<i>Mr. Sandman</i>

272
00:24:07,404 --> 00:24:09,072
<i>Bring me a dream</i>

273
00:24:09,865 --> 00:24:12,701
<i>Make him the cutest</i>
<i>That I've ever seen…</i>

274
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:15,328
<i>Ten years after Japan's defeat,</i>

275
00:24:15,412 --> 00:24:17,372
<i>we finally began to recover,</i>

276
00:24:17,456 --> 00:24:19,541
<i>and a city was reborn from the ashes.</i>

277
00:24:19,624 --> 00:24:21,918
<i>That his lonesome nights are over…</i>

278
00:24:22,586 --> 00:24:24,629
<i>Once people's hunger</i>
<i>had finally been sated,</i>

279
00:24:25,213 --> 00:24:27,090
<i>desire began to take control of them.</i>

280
00:24:27,174 --> 00:24:29,551
<i>Don't have nobody to call my own…</i>

281
00:24:29,634 --> 00:24:30,719
<i>Desire?</i>

282
00:24:31,553 --> 00:24:32,596
<i>Yes.</i>

283
00:24:33,263 --> 00:24:34,681
<i>When you attain one thing,</i>

284
00:24:34,764 --> 00:24:37,350
<i>it's human nature</i>
<i>to start craving another.</i>

285
00:24:37,893 --> 00:24:39,019
<i>It's a cycle.</i>

286
00:24:39,102 --> 00:24:41,354
<i>We just want more, more!</i>

287
00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:47,694
- Thank you for coming.
- Okay, thank you.

288
00:24:47,777 --> 00:24:49,779
- It was delicious.
- Please come back again sometime.

289
00:24:49,863 --> 00:24:51,114
Thank you very much.

290
00:24:51,198 --> 00:24:53,074
Oh, Sachiko, the front tables.

291
00:24:53,158 --> 00:24:54,075
Uh-huh.

292
00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:11,593
Twenty-eight seconds!

293
00:25:11,676 --> 00:25:13,970
She brought herself to tears.
It's incredible!

294
00:25:14,971 --> 00:25:16,139
Kazuko, well done!

295
00:25:16,223 --> 00:25:19,768
I told you, making yourself cry
is very simple to do.

296
00:25:19,851 --> 00:25:22,854
Gentlemen, I believe you each owe me
a hundred yen as promised!

297
00:25:22,938 --> 00:25:25,398
Pay up! Pay up!

298
00:25:25,482 --> 00:25:27,025
Thank you! Thanks a lot!

299
00:25:27,108 --> 00:25:29,861
Kazuko, don't you dare
take money from customers!

300
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:32,697
- Come on, now!
- It's all good. Mine, relax.

301
00:25:32,781 --> 00:25:35,951
Nakazono, please stop encouraging her!
I don't like it.

302
00:25:36,034 --> 00:25:38,411
They made the bet,
and she won fair and square.

303
00:25:38,912 --> 00:25:40,830
Boy, she'd make a hell of an actress, huh?

304
00:25:40,914 --> 00:25:43,667
Are you kidding?
You'd be great. That's a fact!

305
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:46,294
When you become famous,
don't forget to come and drink with us!

306
00:25:46,378 --> 00:25:49,881
Hmm. I don't know about that. Who knows?

307
00:25:50,924 --> 00:25:53,009
If she was a star,
she wouldn't be hanging around here.

308
00:25:53,093 --> 00:25:55,303
- You can bet on that.
- Exactly. Thank you.

309
00:25:55,387 --> 00:25:58,390
I'd be with other actors.
You know, 'cause they'd be famous too.

310
00:25:58,473 --> 00:26:00,809
Now, don't be ridiculous! Come on!

311
00:26:00,892 --> 00:26:03,812
Would you stop indulging my daughter
before it's too late?

312
00:26:03,895 --> 00:26:05,730
We talked,
and she's getting a job after school.

313
00:26:05,814 --> 00:26:07,857
- I'm back.
- Great. Thank you.

314
00:26:07,941 --> 00:26:10,318
Akiko, are you okay?
You look pale as a ghost.

315
00:26:10,402 --> 00:26:11,486
Do you feel feverish?

316
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:13,780
Mom, do you mind
if I go rest for a little while?

317
00:26:13,863 --> 00:26:16,199
Are you all right, honey?
You can go rest. We're okay here.

318
00:26:16,283 --> 00:26:17,409
I'm okay. I'm just tired.

319
00:26:17,492 --> 00:26:19,244
Once I sleep a bit,
I can come back and help.

320
00:26:19,327 --> 00:26:21,413
Wait, wait! Hold on, Akiko!

321
00:26:21,496 --> 00:26:22,581
Yes, what?

322
00:26:22,664 --> 00:26:25,667
- You should rest at home. It'll be better.
- I said I'm fine, Mom. Don't worry!

323
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:27,544
Akiko, wait!

324
00:26:27,627 --> 00:26:29,671
Is her day job really that hard on her?

325
00:26:29,754 --> 00:26:31,923
She's been working overtime every day.

326
00:26:32,549 --> 00:26:34,301
Well, with the Korean War going on,

327
00:26:34,384 --> 00:26:36,720
it's been very busy
for all these factories.

328
00:26:37,220 --> 00:26:38,555
They're working her like a dog,

329
00:26:38,638 --> 00:26:41,016
and she's barely getting paid
for any of it.

330
00:26:41,558 --> 00:26:43,351
It's true. The economy may be booming,

331
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:45,854
but the workers
aren't seeing much of that money.

332
00:26:47,314 --> 00:26:49,649
Well, Akiko might be all right
ending up like that,

333
00:26:49,733 --> 00:26:51,192
but I'm certainly not.

334
00:26:51,776 --> 00:26:54,779
Yes, but it's still her hours and paycheck
that's keeping you all in school,

335
00:26:54,863 --> 00:26:56,281
is it not?

336
00:26:56,364 --> 00:26:57,824
You should be grateful.

337
00:27:00,994 --> 00:27:02,037
Sorry for the wait.

338
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:03,330
Ah!

339
00:27:05,498 --> 00:27:07,125
Sit down. Have a drink.

340
00:27:07,792 --> 00:27:09,419
No. I've got another customer lined up.

341
00:27:09,502 --> 00:27:11,379
Besides, I can already see the lust
in your eyes.

342
00:27:11,463 --> 00:27:12,881
All right.

343
00:27:12,964 --> 00:27:14,591
Thanks. You were great.

344
00:27:14,674 --> 00:27:15,592
Bye.

345
00:27:15,675 --> 00:27:17,844
See ya. Maybe on the big screen!

346
00:27:17,927 --> 00:27:19,304
- Come on.
- Thanks for coming in!

347
00:27:19,387 --> 00:27:20,889
All right, all right!

348
00:27:20,972 --> 00:27:23,141
Jeez, that guy won't stop!

349
00:27:23,224 --> 00:27:26,102
I'd rather spend my money
on booze than women.

350
00:27:27,437 --> 00:27:28,813
Kazuko, another round?

351
00:27:28,897 --> 00:27:29,856
Sure.

352
00:27:40,075 --> 00:27:42,452
Kazuko, what's your plan
after you finish high school?

353
00:27:42,535 --> 00:27:44,621
Uh, oh…

354
00:27:45,246 --> 00:27:47,791
Are you serious about becoming an actress?

355
00:27:50,752 --> 00:27:53,463
Well, I know
it's not the easiest business to get into.

356
00:27:53,963 --> 00:27:55,006
But…

357
00:27:57,008 --> 00:27:58,176
Mm…

358
00:27:58,259 --> 00:28:01,054
Money's the most important thing of all.
That's all I really need.

359
00:28:02,180 --> 00:28:03,598
Money, huh?

360
00:28:15,485 --> 00:28:17,320
Come on, people! Let's go! Move it!

361
00:28:17,404 --> 00:28:18,780
Shut up, move!

362
00:28:21,157 --> 00:28:22,283
Come on, keep moving!

363
00:28:22,367 --> 00:28:24,202
Move it! Let's go!

364
00:28:24,828 --> 00:28:26,454
Hey! Get outta the way!

365
00:28:27,205 --> 00:28:28,581
All of you need to move!

366
00:28:29,374 --> 00:28:31,167
Come on, move it. Go!

367
00:28:36,631 --> 00:28:39,843
SECOND NEW FACE CONTEST
LOOKING FOR NEW STARS

368
00:28:39,926 --> 00:28:42,846
CABARET WHITE GLOVE
HIRING HOSTESSES

369
00:28:47,976 --> 00:28:53,148
HIGH EARNINGS
AGE 20 AND UP

370
00:29:58,129 --> 00:29:59,047
Hello.

371
00:29:59,589 --> 00:30:01,299
Sorry, who's in charge here?

372
00:30:02,884 --> 00:30:04,135
How can I help you?

373
00:30:11,351 --> 00:30:12,894
RESUME: KAZUKO HOSOKI
APRIL 4, 1935

374
00:30:12,977 --> 00:30:14,354
20 years old?

375
00:30:20,568 --> 00:30:21,903
You're still in school, aren't ya?

376
00:30:22,695 --> 00:30:23,696
No.

377
00:30:27,116 --> 00:30:29,994
Don't worry.
We'll say you're 20 in here, okay?

378
00:30:36,751 --> 00:30:38,044
When can you start?

379
00:30:38,586 --> 00:30:40,922
Oh. Whenever you need me to.

380
00:30:41,005 --> 00:30:42,549
Good. You're hired.

381
00:30:43,758 --> 00:30:45,385
Thank you so much!

382
00:30:45,885 --> 00:30:48,346
From the look of it,
you've never worn makeup before.

383
00:30:50,598 --> 00:30:52,851
I'll teach you. Don't worry about it.

384
00:30:56,896 --> 00:31:00,567
Uh, sir, before I start,
there's one thing I wanna be clear about.

385
00:31:01,150 --> 00:31:01,985
What's that?

386
00:31:02,068 --> 00:31:03,736
Well, I just…

387
00:31:03,820 --> 00:31:05,196
I won't sell my body.

388
00:31:05,697 --> 00:31:06,573
Understood?

389
00:31:10,493 --> 00:31:13,288
Understood. You don't have to worry.
That's not the kind of place we are.

390
00:31:16,583 --> 00:31:18,042
Hello!

391
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:20,420
Oh. A new girl?

392
00:31:20,503 --> 00:31:21,546
Yes.

393
00:31:22,338 --> 00:31:25,258
This is Kazuko.
She'll be starting with us today.

394
00:31:25,341 --> 00:31:28,386
And, Kazuko,
this is our number one hostess, Lily.

395
00:31:29,178 --> 00:31:30,680
It's nice to meet you.

396
00:31:31,180 --> 00:31:33,308
This is your first time
doing this kind of work,

397
00:31:33,391 --> 00:31:34,726
from the looks of it.

398
00:31:35,476 --> 00:31:37,604
Well, I'm used to serving people.

399
00:31:37,687 --> 00:31:40,106
My family runs an <i>oden </i>bar,
and I've helped them out for years.

400
00:31:40,189 --> 00:31:41,190
<i>Oden</i>?

401
00:31:43,484 --> 00:31:45,111
Oh, come on.

402
00:31:45,695 --> 00:31:46,779
Listen to me, Lily.

403
00:31:46,863 --> 00:31:49,198
You're to take good care of this girl.
Do you understand?

404
00:31:49,282 --> 00:31:50,700
Yeah, yeah.

405
00:32:04,505 --> 00:32:05,965
- Welcome!
- Come on in, gentlemen!

406
00:32:06,049 --> 00:32:07,300
- Come on in, please!
- Welcome!

407
00:32:07,383 --> 00:32:09,510
- Enjoy your evening!
- Come in and enjoy.

408
00:32:10,136 --> 00:32:12,639
- Good to see you back, sir. Enjoy.
- You take care.

409
00:32:13,389 --> 00:32:14,390
Open your mouth.

410
00:32:44,253 --> 00:32:45,213
Hmm.

411
00:32:58,726 --> 00:33:00,853
Well, would ya look at that?
You're a lady.

412
00:33:05,942 --> 00:33:08,152
All right. Now head over to table five.

413
00:33:08,236 --> 00:33:10,113
- You'll do good.
- Thanks.

414
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:27,440
- Yokoyama-san.
- Hmm?

415
00:34:28,191 --> 00:34:30,860
You've been so distant recently.
What's going on?

416
00:34:30,943 --> 00:34:33,613
You don't even ask me
out to dinner anymore.

417
00:34:34,697 --> 00:34:36,699
You haven't replaced me
with a newer model, have you?

418
00:34:36,783 --> 00:34:38,659
Mm, I've just been busy with work.

419
00:34:38,743 --> 00:34:40,578
- That's all.
- Mm.

420
00:34:40,661 --> 00:34:43,372
All right.
Let's meet before your shift next week.

421
00:34:44,040 --> 00:34:44,999
- Really?
- Yeah.

422
00:34:45,083 --> 00:34:47,335
I'm so excited!

423
00:34:48,711 --> 00:34:50,713
So how old are you, young lady?

424
00:34:50,797 --> 00:34:51,756
I'm 20.

425
00:34:51,839 --> 00:34:53,466
Ah. Just entering adulthood.

426
00:34:53,549 --> 00:34:55,259
Lucky you. I miss that.

427
00:34:56,886 --> 00:34:58,846
So what do you do when you're not here?

428
00:34:58,930 --> 00:34:59,764
Oh.

429
00:35:00,515 --> 00:35:02,975
Um, I work in an office.

430
00:35:03,059 --> 00:35:04,060
I see.

431
00:35:04,602 --> 00:35:06,896
Juggling two jobs must be tough.

432
00:35:06,979 --> 00:35:09,941
Well, I've got to earn money
for my brother and sister's tuition.

433
00:35:10,024 --> 00:35:14,028
Let's not talk about
your family issues right now, Kazuko.

434
00:35:14,529 --> 00:35:16,489
Yokoyama-san came here to unwind.

435
00:35:16,572 --> 00:35:18,324
No. It's okay. I want to know.

436
00:35:19,283 --> 00:35:21,119
So your brother and sister are in school?

437
00:35:21,202 --> 00:35:22,870
Honey, the ashtray.

438
00:35:22,954 --> 00:35:24,247
It's full.

439
00:35:25,206 --> 00:35:28,584
Oh dear.
You're blind as a bat, aren't you?

440
00:35:30,586 --> 00:35:32,713
Yokoyama-san, come on. Let's go dance.

441
00:35:32,797 --> 00:35:34,215
Sure.

442
00:35:55,319 --> 00:35:56,696
Hey, Ochiai.

443
00:35:57,238 --> 00:35:59,991
What can you tell me
about the guest sitting at my table?

444
00:36:02,869 --> 00:36:06,455
Oh. He's the president of a company
called Yokoyama Textile.

445
00:36:07,456 --> 00:36:08,916
He may not look it now,

446
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:11,419
but rumor has it,
he had a pretty rough upbringing.

447
00:36:14,547 --> 00:36:15,548
Something wrong?

448
00:36:16,257 --> 00:36:17,258
No.

449
00:36:35,234 --> 00:36:41,574
RAT POISON

450
00:36:48,623 --> 00:36:50,666
Oh, Kazuko.

451
00:36:51,334 --> 00:36:54,462
What could've possibly kept you
out this late?

452
00:36:55,213 --> 00:36:57,924
Is that… Are you wearing makeup?

453
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:00,885
I'm working at a cabaret now.

454
00:37:01,510 --> 00:37:02,386
A cabaret?

455
00:37:02,470 --> 00:37:04,305
Relax, Mom. It's not a sleazy place, okay?

456
00:37:04,388 --> 00:37:06,849
I'll still go to school during the day
like we discussed.

457
00:37:06,933 --> 00:37:10,144
I might not be at the bar like I used to,
but I'll bring home more money this way.

458
00:37:10,228 --> 00:37:12,188
We need to talk about this.
You can't just run off!

459
00:37:12,271 --> 00:37:15,650
- I'm tired, okay? Good night, Mom.
- Uh! Wait, Kazuko! Uh…

460
00:37:44,887 --> 00:37:46,222
Um, good morning.

461
00:37:46,764 --> 00:37:49,475
Could you put me through
to President Yokoyama?

462
00:37:56,148 --> 00:37:57,608
There you are. Enjoy.

463
00:37:58,526 --> 00:38:00,111
Welcome, sir. This way, please.

464
00:38:00,194 --> 00:38:02,613
Sorry for calling you
out of the blue, sir.

465
00:38:03,614 --> 00:38:05,199
No worries at all.

466
00:38:05,866 --> 00:38:06,993
How can I help you?

467
00:38:07,493 --> 00:38:09,161
I'm not really sure.

468
00:38:09,662 --> 00:38:13,916
I just felt it would be beneficial
to have someone listen to my story.

469
00:38:15,418 --> 00:38:18,671
And when I started thinking
about who I could trust,

470
00:38:19,255 --> 00:38:21,090
your face came into my mind.

471
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:23,884
Fair enough.

472
00:38:25,845 --> 00:38:27,346
Well, please. Go ahead.

473
00:38:31,559 --> 00:38:32,935
It was hard

474
00:38:34,312 --> 00:38:36,147
growing up in my family.

475
00:38:37,481 --> 00:38:38,524
We were so poor.

476
00:38:38,607 --> 00:38:42,361
And after the war,
I thought we would starve to death.

477
00:38:44,655 --> 00:38:45,614
Ah.

478
00:38:47,241 --> 00:38:49,618
I'm sorry for unloading on you like this.

479
00:38:50,369 --> 00:38:52,747
- What am I even trying to say?
- Mm.

480
00:38:54,498 --> 00:38:57,126
I've been there, ya know.

481
00:39:00,796 --> 00:39:04,091
I had a tough childhood too.
Way back in the day.

482
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:08,095
All I could do was work, work, work.

483
00:39:08,596 --> 00:39:10,681
It's how I ended up where I am now.

484
00:39:12,350 --> 00:39:15,853
I imagine you know what that's like.
You've got to keep at it.

485
00:39:16,854 --> 00:39:18,022
Kazuko.

486
00:39:18,522 --> 00:39:19,690
What's the matter?

487
00:39:20,649 --> 00:39:21,984
It's nothing. I…

488
00:39:23,277 --> 00:39:26,781
It just means so much
to hear someone like you say that.

489
00:39:37,375 --> 00:39:38,376
Thank you.

490
00:39:38,876 --> 00:39:40,461
Ah. Thank you very much.

491
00:39:40,544 --> 00:39:42,671
I appreciate that, sir.
Have a great night.

492
00:39:42,755 --> 00:39:44,006
Thank you, gentlemen.

493
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:45,424
Have a good time.

494
00:39:57,436 --> 00:39:58,604
Let's dance!

495
00:40:00,564 --> 00:40:01,649
Come on!

496
00:40:13,828 --> 00:40:14,787
Perfect!

497
00:40:35,474 --> 00:40:36,684
Yeah!

498
00:40:38,394 --> 00:40:39,437
Very good!

499
00:41:20,352 --> 00:41:21,770
Oh!

500
00:41:22,897 --> 00:41:24,356
Oh! Uh, uh…

501
00:41:25,357 --> 00:41:26,317
Ooh! Oh!

502
00:41:30,279 --> 00:41:31,322
Oh!

503
00:41:32,615 --> 00:41:33,741
Whoa!

504
00:41:34,950 --> 00:41:36,494
Whoo!

505
00:41:37,161 --> 00:41:38,245
Whoo!

506
00:41:54,637 --> 00:41:57,139
All right. I'm very pleased to report

507
00:41:57,806 --> 00:42:00,768
that last month's sales
set an all-time record.

508
00:42:04,730 --> 00:42:07,816
Of course, this is all thanks
to your hard work.

509
00:42:07,900 --> 00:42:09,568
Thank you all very much.

510
00:42:10,319 --> 00:42:11,487
Now, then.

511
00:42:12,112 --> 00:42:15,282
It's time
for the results you've been waiting for.

512
00:42:15,366 --> 00:42:18,744
Which one of you
had the highest number of reserved tables?

513
00:42:19,954 --> 00:42:21,038
Kazuko.

514
00:42:23,707 --> 00:42:24,792
Step forward.

515
00:42:31,298 --> 00:42:32,675
Congratulations.

516
00:42:34,343 --> 00:42:35,594
Keep up the good work.

517
00:42:36,303 --> 00:42:37,346
Thanks.

518
00:42:56,198 --> 00:42:57,908
Good evening, ladies.

519
00:42:58,701 --> 00:43:00,494
- Hey there.
- Good evening.

520
00:43:05,916 --> 00:43:08,419
Hey, do any of you smell something?

521
00:43:08,502 --> 00:43:09,962
Oh my God. I know, right?

522
00:43:10,045 --> 00:43:11,922
It stinks. What the hell is that?

523
00:43:12,006 --> 00:43:14,258
Daikon radish? <i>Konnyaku?</i>

524
00:43:15,551 --> 00:43:16,885
Oh.

525
00:43:16,969 --> 00:43:18,929
I know. It's <i>oden.</i>

526
00:43:19,763 --> 00:43:20,973
Ugh.

527
00:43:21,056 --> 00:43:22,808
Reeks of poverty.

528
00:43:24,310 --> 00:43:28,230
Gosh, it makes you wonder
if that terrible odor ever goes away.

529
00:43:30,024 --> 00:43:31,358
Good night.

530
00:43:32,901 --> 00:43:34,111
Good night.

531
00:43:52,212 --> 00:43:56,050
Ochiai-san, would it be all right
if I borrowed this outfit for the night?

532
00:43:56,842 --> 00:43:57,885
Oh…

533
00:43:58,761 --> 00:44:00,387
Sure. I suppose so.

534
00:44:00,471 --> 00:44:01,555
Thank you. Good night.

535
00:44:03,682 --> 00:44:04,767
Kazuko.

536
00:44:06,143 --> 00:44:07,311
Uh, what's wrong?

537
00:44:08,854 --> 00:44:09,772
Hmm.

538
00:44:10,564 --> 00:44:11,523
I see.

539
00:44:15,319 --> 00:44:16,528
All right.

540
00:44:17,613 --> 00:44:19,323
I'll tell the ladies to cut it out.

541
00:44:20,157 --> 00:44:22,618
It won't make a difference.

542
00:44:23,410 --> 00:44:26,288
They'll never admit they did it
in a million years.

543
00:44:26,955 --> 00:44:27,790
Don't worry.

544
00:44:31,335 --> 00:44:33,087
I won't let anything happen to you.

545
00:44:40,636 --> 00:44:41,679
Kazuko.

546
00:44:42,388 --> 00:44:43,806
What are you doing this weekend?

547
00:44:57,528 --> 00:45:01,365
<i>Earth angel, earth angel</i>

548
00:45:01,949 --> 00:45:03,117
<i>Will you be mine…</i>

549
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:04,952
That dress looks great on you.

550
00:45:06,453 --> 00:45:10,916
Yes, but… look at the price.
I can't afford to buy it.

551
00:45:12,459 --> 00:45:14,002
Let me buy it for you.

552
00:45:14,545 --> 00:45:16,338
To celebrate you being number one.

553
00:45:19,216 --> 00:45:21,218
You and I are gonna stroll around town,

554
00:45:22,052 --> 00:45:23,429
and you're gonna wear that.

555
00:45:23,512 --> 00:45:24,972
<i>Earth angel</i>

556
00:45:25,639 --> 00:45:27,725
<i>The one I adore…</i>

557
00:45:27,808 --> 00:45:28,976
Thanks for your help.

558
00:45:29,059 --> 00:45:30,853
<i>Love you forever</i>

559
00:45:30,936 --> 00:45:33,814
<i>And ever more…</i>

560
00:45:33,897 --> 00:45:35,691
Do you come to Ginza often?

561
00:45:36,734 --> 00:45:39,570
This isn't the sort of place
you drop by casually.

562
00:45:40,112 --> 00:45:41,905
The people, the shops…

563
00:45:42,406 --> 00:45:44,700
Only the best of the best come to Ginza.

564
00:45:45,909 --> 00:45:48,287
Just walking these streets
makes you feel special, doesn't it?

565
00:45:48,370 --> 00:45:50,122
Mm-hmm. Definitely.

566
00:45:50,205 --> 00:45:52,791
I know I'd feel out of place
if I wasn't wearing this dress.

567
00:45:53,292 --> 00:45:55,502
Would you like to buy some flowers?

568
00:45:58,756 --> 00:45:59,757
Thank you.

569
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:01,258
Here.

570
00:46:02,050 --> 00:46:04,178
Thank you. Have a nice day!

571
00:46:05,220 --> 00:46:06,638
For you.

572
00:46:07,264 --> 00:46:08,265
Thank you.

573
00:46:08,766 --> 00:46:10,684
<i>Oh, oh</i>

574
00:46:10,768 --> 00:46:12,060
<i>Earth angel…</i>

575
00:46:12,144 --> 00:46:16,523
You know, I always said that one day
I'd open my own place in Ginza.

576
00:46:16,607 --> 00:46:18,692
Oh! That sounds nice.

577
00:46:18,776 --> 00:46:20,194
It's gonna happen. You'll see.

578
00:46:20,277 --> 00:46:22,613
<i>Love you all the time…</i>

579
00:46:22,696 --> 00:46:25,699
And when it does, I want you with me.

580
00:46:26,784 --> 00:46:29,077
<i>A fool in love</i>

581
00:46:29,161 --> 00:46:32,039
<i>With you</i>

582
00:46:35,918 --> 00:46:38,545
<i>I fell for you</i>

583
00:46:39,046 --> 00:46:40,506
<i>And I knew</i>

584
00:46:48,722 --> 00:46:50,849
Ochiai, wait. I…

585
00:46:50,933 --> 00:46:51,809
I know.

586
00:46:53,393 --> 00:46:54,645
It's your first time.

587
00:48:11,096 --> 00:48:12,055
Hey.

588
00:48:13,265 --> 00:48:15,267
What sort of books do you like reading?

589
00:48:17,102 --> 00:48:18,020
Uh…

590
00:48:21,773 --> 00:48:22,691
Mm.

591
00:48:25,152 --> 00:48:27,905
Mm. <i>Anna Karenina.</i>

592
00:48:29,197 --> 00:48:30,407
What's it about?

593
00:48:31,575 --> 00:48:32,534
Hmm.

594
00:48:33,869 --> 00:48:36,121
Well, to put it simply,

595
00:48:37,456 --> 00:48:40,000
it's the story of a woman

596
00:48:40,876 --> 00:48:43,003
who falls into a living hell.

597
00:48:47,049 --> 00:48:48,133
You know what?

598
00:48:48,884 --> 00:48:50,719
You sort of remind me of Anna.

599
00:48:50,802 --> 00:48:52,512
No way!

600
00:48:52,596 --> 00:48:55,015
No. There's no "living hell" in my future.

601
00:49:00,145 --> 00:49:01,229
One day,

602
00:49:02,272 --> 00:49:04,858
you and I'll have that place in Ginza.

603
00:49:07,361 --> 00:49:10,822
If we wanna do that,
we're gonna need lots of funding.

604
00:49:11,365 --> 00:49:12,366
Mm.

605
00:49:15,452 --> 00:49:17,162
I'm gonna make loads of money.

606
00:49:22,459 --> 00:49:25,963
How ya doing tonight, sir?
The girls'll be thrilled to see ya!

607
00:49:26,046 --> 00:49:29,132
- Have a great night, now.
- Welcome, sir. Come on in!

608
00:49:29,216 --> 00:49:31,051
Yes, sir. Best girls in town.

609
00:49:36,890 --> 00:49:38,976
- Thank you for everything.
- Thank you.

610
00:49:39,059 --> 00:49:40,936
- Maybe you can take me out.
- Absolutely.

611
00:49:41,019 --> 00:49:43,480
I'll gladly take you
anywhere you want to go.

612
00:49:43,563 --> 00:49:45,190
- You're sweet.
- All right, then.

613
00:49:45,273 --> 00:49:46,441
- Thank you.
- Good night.

614
00:49:46,525 --> 00:49:48,402
Good night. Please come back anytime.

615
00:49:48,485 --> 00:49:49,361
I will.

616
00:49:49,444 --> 00:49:51,697
- Thanks for coming in.
- Get home safe now.

617
00:50:12,968 --> 00:50:15,012
Please don't do that, Yokoyama-san.

618
00:50:17,139 --> 00:50:20,434
Kazuko, we're going back to my hotel.

619
00:50:21,977 --> 00:50:24,354
You know I don't do that.
Please cut it out.

620
00:50:25,230 --> 00:50:28,316
You do it now.
It's already been figured out.

621
00:50:30,569 --> 00:50:31,987
So, from now on,

622
00:50:32,070 --> 00:50:35,282
you'll be spending a night with me
once per week.

623
00:50:35,365 --> 00:50:37,743
And each month, you'll receive 20,000 yen.

624
00:50:39,536 --> 00:50:42,164
Don't worry.
I already paid Ochiai up front.

625
00:50:44,791 --> 00:50:45,792
Okay?

626
00:50:52,049 --> 00:50:53,675
You sold me?

627
00:50:54,676 --> 00:50:56,511
- Tell me it's not true!
- Kazuko, listen!

628
00:50:56,595 --> 00:50:57,763
Okay, come here.

629
00:51:00,390 --> 00:51:02,559
Do you have anything to say for yourself?

630
00:51:03,310 --> 00:51:05,312
You said you'd make loads of money,
didn't you?

631
00:51:05,395 --> 00:51:08,315
- I never agreed to sell my body for you!
- It's for our dream, Kazuko!

632
00:51:08,398 --> 00:51:11,234
What? Did you think that money
was just gonna fall from the sky?

633
00:51:15,197 --> 00:51:16,198
Grow up.

634
00:51:36,301 --> 00:51:39,513
Someone looks like they've snapped out
of a sweet little fantasy.

635
00:51:41,681 --> 00:51:43,016
Just so you know,

636
00:51:43,975 --> 00:51:46,478
it's not the first time
Ochiai's done this.

637
00:51:48,730 --> 00:51:51,817
He finds some sweet little thing
who he knows will make bank,

638
00:51:51,900 --> 00:51:54,611
makes them fall for him,
and then sells them off.

639
00:51:57,823 --> 00:52:02,077
And the only reason I bullied you
is 'cause Ochiai ordered me to.

640
00:52:02,786 --> 00:52:05,997
Acting like some white knight,
saving the poor, young, bullied girl

641
00:52:06,081 --> 00:52:08,375
is the number one trick in his playbook.

642
00:52:10,961 --> 00:52:12,796
Your first date was in Ginza, wasn't it?

643
00:52:14,798 --> 00:52:18,552
Did he regale you with fantasies
of opening a business there together?

644
00:52:21,304 --> 00:52:23,181
Being Yokayama's side girl?

645
00:52:23,807 --> 00:52:25,642
That'd earn a lot of dough.

646
00:53:48,975 --> 00:53:50,310
Oh. There you are.

647
00:53:52,145 --> 00:53:53,146
Good.

648
00:53:54,481 --> 00:53:57,776
You disappeared all of a sudden.
I… I was worried.

649
00:53:58,485 --> 00:54:00,320
Look, maybe we should talk about--

650
00:54:00,820 --> 00:54:02,447
What the hell are you doing?

651
00:54:04,157 --> 00:54:04,991
MOBIL KEROSENE

652
00:54:05,075 --> 00:54:05,909
Jesus.

653
00:54:07,577 --> 00:54:08,745
Babe, stop.

654
00:54:10,330 --> 00:54:11,581
Stop!

655
00:54:11,665 --> 00:54:14,000
Please stop! Please!

656
00:54:14,584 --> 00:54:16,544
I… I'm sorry, okay!

657
00:54:16,628 --> 00:54:19,256
I… I was wrong! Please don't!

658
00:54:19,339 --> 00:54:21,508
Please! I'm begging you!

659
00:54:22,175 --> 00:54:23,426
I'm sorry, please!

660
00:54:23,510 --> 00:54:25,095
Kazuko!

661
00:54:25,178 --> 00:54:28,223
Please! Please! Don't burn me! Please!

662
00:54:28,306 --> 00:54:31,017
Oh God, please!

663
00:54:35,105 --> 00:54:37,607
- I'm sorry! I'm sorry!
- Pathetic man.

664
00:55:26,281 --> 00:55:29,367
RAT POISON

665
00:56:28,343 --> 00:56:31,304
The first man I ever slept with
tried to sell me off.

666
00:56:32,180 --> 00:56:34,307
Well, people who get conned

667
00:56:34,391 --> 00:56:36,559
are more at fault
than the ones who do the conning.

668
00:56:38,561 --> 00:56:41,523
So… did you survive?

669
00:56:41,606 --> 00:56:42,899
Oh, come on.

670
00:56:42,982 --> 00:56:45,944
- If I'd died, I wouldn't be here now.
- Oh.

671
00:56:46,444 --> 00:56:48,696
Right. That's obvious.

672
00:56:50,031 --> 00:56:51,908
I was young and naive back then.

673
00:56:52,534 --> 00:56:54,411
And the truth is, it was stupid.

674
00:57:05,422 --> 00:57:07,465
So you really tried to kill yourself?

675
00:57:08,800 --> 00:57:10,009
What do you mean?

676
00:57:14,431 --> 00:57:16,808
For someone who attempted suicide
to go on TV

677
00:57:16,891 --> 00:57:19,561
and say to a girl,
"You'll end up killing yourself,"

678
00:57:20,061 --> 00:57:21,813
just seems crazy to me.

679
00:57:23,314 --> 00:57:24,399
Uozumi!

680
00:57:25,400 --> 00:57:27,986
I'm so sorry, ma'am.
That was inappropriate.

681
00:57:29,028 --> 00:57:31,489
You know, I could tell
when I first saw you

682
00:57:32,198 --> 00:57:33,575
that you've got real guts.

683
00:57:39,622 --> 00:57:41,499
I told that girl a fact.

684
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:44,794
She'd better be careful
or she'll end up like I did.

685
00:57:45,503 --> 00:57:47,547
I was only trying to warn her

686
00:57:48,173 --> 00:57:50,133
before she makes any more mistakes.

687
00:57:56,055 --> 00:57:58,475
What happened
after you tried to kill yourself?
